British Prime Minister Theresa May is expected on Friday to announce her departure from office, 'The Times' reported, without citing a source. LONDON - British Prime Minister Theresa May is expected on Friday to announce her departure from office, The Times reported, without citing a source. May will remain as prime minister while her successor is elected in a two-stage process under which two final candidates face a ballot of 125,000 Conservative Party members, the newspaper said.